        <div class="row">
            <h5>The Symbol of Strength</h5>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <p>The image or description of “strength” has been used as an honor bestowed upon Black women to represent the unrecognition “of their humanity and the violations they experience within their families and communities.” In a way, it says that Black women are strong and that they can endure abuse and mistreatment to be able to continue providing the support and help that their families have depended upon since the beginning. At face value, the stereotype appears as encouragement for Black women to be independent and to break the glass ceiling. However, the stereotype forces Black women to conform and deny themselves as they seek to address and solve the plights facing the Black family and community. </p>
        </div>

